<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - LO RANGE SPEED GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="3">
        <title>LO RANGE SPEED GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive or press against the rear of the output shaft to move
                assembly forward and from the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302994">Figure 94</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302994" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302994" filename="../figg13/G1302994.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 94. Press Against Rear of Output Shaft to Move Assembly Forward</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When applying force to the rear of the output shaft, DO NOT DAMAGE THREADS.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear washer and LO Range speed gear from the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302995">Figure 95</hotlnk>). Remove the spline washer from the hub of the reduction
                gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302995">inset</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302995" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302995" filename="../figg13/G1302995.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 95. Remove Rear Washer and LO Range Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the output shaft rear bearing to the rear and out of the housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302996">Figure 96</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302996" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302996" filename="../figg13/G1302996.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 96. Move Output Shaft Rear Bearing to Rear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
